## Propagating Trace Context Across RabbitMQ

The key is to inject the current trace context into RabbitMQ message headers on publish, then extract it on consume to link the spans.

**Service A (Publisher):**

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;
using OpenTelemetry;
using OpenTelemetry.Context.Propagation;
using RabbitMQ.Client;

// Create an ActivitySource for your publisher
private static readonly ActivitySource ActivitySource = new("ServiceA.Messaging");
private static readonly TextMapPropagator Propagator = Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator;

public void PublishOrder(OrderEvent order)
{
    using var activity = ActivitySource.StartActivity("OrderPublished send", ActivityKind.Producer);

    var props = _channel.CreateBasicProperties();
    props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

    // Inject current trace context into message headers
    Propagator.Inject(
        new PropagationContext(activity.Context, Baggage.Current),
        props.Headers,
        (headers, key, value) => headers[key] = value);

    var body = JsonSerializer.SerializeToUtf8Bytes(order);
    _channel.BasicPublish(exchange: "orders", routingKey: "order.created", basicProperties: props, body: body);
}
```

**Service B (Consumer):**

```csharp
private static readonly ActivitySource ActivitySource = new("ServiceB.Messaging");
private static readonly TextMapPropagator Propagator = Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator;

public void HandleMessage(BasicDeliverEventArgs ea)
{
    // Extract trace context from message headers
    var parentContext = Propagator.Extract(
        default,
        ea.BasicProperties.Headers,
        (headers, key) =>
        {
            if (headers != null && headers.TryGetValue(key, out var value))
            {
                return new[] { Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])value) };
            }
            return Enumerable.Empty<string>();
        });

    // Restore context and start a linked span
    Baggage.Current = parentContext.Baggage;
    using var activity = ActivitySource.StartActivity(
        "OrderPublished receive",
        ActivityKind.Consumer,
        parentContext.ActivityContext);  // <-- links the trace

    // Process message...
}
```

**Registration (both services in `Program.cs`):**

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(tracing => tracing
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Messaging")   // or ServiceB.Messaging
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

**Why this works:** The W3C `traceparent`/`tracestate` headers get serialized into the RabbitMQ message properties. The consumer extracts them and passes the parent `ActivityContext` when starting its span, so your trace backend stitches them into one end-to-end trace.

**Note:** RabbitMQ stores header values as `byte[]`, hence the `Encoding.UTF8.GetString` cast on extraction.
